        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 18 at 8:30AM CDT by NWS Lincoln IL</headline>
        <description>At 830 AM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm over
New Philadelphia, or 12 miles east of Macomb, moving northeast at 50
mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and pea size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Fairview, London Mills, Smithfield, Marietta, Ellisville, and Fiatt.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
